commit.message:
Set up Jest test runner (#531)

* Jest setup for unit tests.

* Unit tests for Utils.js.

* Add test command to tools/ui.

* Add UI tests to tools/all_tests.

* Add info on running UI tests to the README.

* Include node and npm dependencies in Docker setup.

* Add jest-cli to npm deps.

Not sure this will work (it already worked in my local Docker, so the only way
to test is by sending it to Travis for real), so this might be reverted.

* Revert "Add jest-cli to npm deps."

This reverts commit 80c8a4ef482fc171297d355a47827e85dd2a5eb8.

It didn't work. Looks like node_modules is missing altogether on Travis.

* Move npm install to after WORKDIR line.

* Revert "Move npm install to after WORKDIR line."

This reverts commit 6d1b44f690490248bc9121e7e12a834ac11590ec.

It accomplished nothing.

* Move npm install to .travis.yml.

* Use setup_10.x for Node.

* Call JS tests X_test.js.
